														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-819516">
									

<p>Some of my favorite SCPs have been deleted and this tripe remains. I'm a little bitter.</p>
<p>The telekill article claims the mass as "9.78&nbsp;g/cm³." Not sure if that matches with iron.</p>
<p>I only mentioned the telekill because there are other SCPs that could legitimately use it (indestructible / actually useful) that have had "requests denied" because the stuff is "scarce." However, if telekill was written exclusively for this SCP (or vice-versa), I could understand the favoritism.</p>
<p>How about, instead of her just oozing a physical manifestation of of her empathy, she actually absorbs the feelings from people, in effect making them feel better.</p>
<p>Or am I completely off base and this is one of those oldies that are immune to criticism because of its age?</p>
<p>Forgive my cynicism. As I said at the start, some (what I could consider) better written and executed SCPs have been deleted and things like this, that only waste resources, remain.</p>

